{"body": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"easily-overridable-templates\">\n<h1>Easily overridable templates<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#easily-overridable-templates\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h1>\n<div class=\"admonition warning\">\n<p class=\"first admonition-title\">Warning</p>\n<p class=\"last\" id=\"1\">This is just a stub document. It will be fleshed out more. If you wish to comment on it, please e-mail coreyoordt at gmail.</p>\n</div>\n<p id=\"2\">Templates are an important part of your pluggable app. They demonstrate how your app works. The more complex your app, the more important templates are. Following a few practices can make your templates very useful. We have two goals: 1. Get demonstrable functionality in as short a time as possible, and 2. modify the fewest templates to do so.</p>\n<p id=\"3\">Instead of putting your templates loose in your templates directory where they can conflict with other apps templates, <strong>* put them in a directory within templates, named after your app to name space them. *</strong> Then you reference them as the relative path from templates, in this case: coolapp/base.html</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-python\"><pre>coolapp\n+-templates\n  +-coolapp\n    +-base.html</pre>\n</div>\n</div>\n", "display_toc": false, "title": "Easily overridable templates", "sourcename": "templates/easily_overridable_templates.txt", "customsidebar": null, "current_page_name": "templates/easily_overridable_templates", "next": {"link": "../extend_one_template/", "title": "Extend one template"}, "rellinks": [["genindex", "General Index", "I", "index"], ["templates/extend_one_template", "Extend one template", "N", "next"], ["templates/index", "Template Patterns", "P", "previous"]], "meta": {}, "parents": [{"link": "../", "title": "Template Patterns"}], "sidebars": null, "toc": "<ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#\">Easily overridable templates</a></li>\n</ul>\n", "prev": {"link": "../", "title": "Template Patterns"}, "metatags": ""}